f0857495-00e9-5c85-849b-5ad843221e1f,tg:rubgr:2794,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Bruegel & Massys Followers. An early attempt at large figure composition influenced by Massys and followers as e.g. Jan Massys & Hemessen, partly parallel with Bosch influneces 'Cutting the Stone', Doyen de Renaix (Bast. 1921) 1556 or 1557, Witch of Malleghem 1559., 1558 Alchemist, 1559 Elck; Late reminiscence in [onleesbaar] 1565; This 1556-58/9 group stylistically rather isolated in B's work. column4: <content>Bruegel & Massys Followers. An early attempt at large figure composition influenced by Massys and followers as e.g. Jan Massys & Hemessen, partly parallel with Bosch influneces 'Cutting the Stone', Doyen de Renaix (Bast. 1921) 1556 or 1557, Witch of Malleghem 1559., 1558 Alchemist, 1559 Elck; Late reminiscence in [onleesbaar] 1565; This 1556-58/9 group stylistically rather isolated in B's work. What about Cornelis Massys?; Marlier, p. 198 Only few paintings by Jan Massys of 1st period (-1544) known, second period 1558ff.</content>
